  "text": "When lure data were analyzed among flights, the difference was significant for flights 1 and 2, but not for flight 3 (Figure 1a (Figure 1f) . Overall, the performance of the L2 lure was similar to the Mega lure under these conditions. Higher catches with L2 lures by the end of the season could be due to a reduced release rate of mating disruption dispensers, since the response threshold of males is dose dependent [CITATION_1] ) and also, high pheromone loads (10X) could have a reduced attraction under this scenario [CITATION_2] . Pear ester alone was comparable to L2 and Mega lures during the first and second flight, but attracted very few moths during the third flight (Figures 1b; 1c;  1d) . Mega lures showed neither a significant improvement compared with L2 lures during both seasons regarding the total number of moth, nor improvement compared to DA2313 lures.",
